# Security headers for static hosts that read a `_headers` file
# (Cloudflare Pages, Netlify). The key privacy line is `connect-src`: the
# browser may only send data back to our own origin ('self') and to
# Cloudflare Web Analytics — never anywhere else, and never user input.
#
# Cloudflare Web Analytics: when enabled in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard,
# Cloudflare auto-injects a tiny, cookieless beacon at the edge (no code or
# token needed here). The beacon loads from static.cloudflareinsights.com and
# POSTs an anonymous page-view (URL, referrer, coarse device class — never
# tool content) to cloudflareinsights.com. The two origins below are exactly
# what that beacon needs; without them the strict CSP silently blocks it and
# the dashboard reports 0 visits. This is "zero egress of USER data": your
# input still physically cannot leave the browser, only an anonymous visit
# ping does.
#
# Note: 'unsafe-inline' for script/style is required by Next.js's static
# runtime (inline bootstrap + styles). 'wasm-unsafe-eval' lets the Hash
# Generator compile its hash-wasm WebAssembly modules in-browser. None of
# these weaken the user-data guarantee — that is enforced by `connect-src`
# allowing only 'self' plus the anonymous-analytics origin.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://cloudflareinsights.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
